title: These bed and breakfast spots in central Pa. make for lavish getaways | Sandy Fenton - PennLive
content:
If you’re looking for a great getaway, you don’t really need to look further than your own backyard.

A couple of months ago, my husband, Stewart, and I went on a central Pa. road trip and stayed overnight at four very different bed & breakfast inns, all members of PABBI (Pa. Association of Bed & Breakfast Inns).

title: Prince Harry ‘has room set aside in luxury hotel where he stays without Meghan Markle near his £12m Ca... - The US Sun
content:
HEIR BNB Prince Harry ‘has room set aside in luxury hotel where he stays without Meghan Markle near his £12m California home’

PRINCE Harry has a room set aside in a luxury hotel where he stays on his own near his California home, it is claimed.

And he has another escape place in LA where he works out and can stay in exclusive bungalows.

3 Prince Harry has a private retreat that he frequents without his wife Meghan Markle Credit: Getty

3 Harry is said to stay at the exclusive San Vicente Bungalows, a private members club in LA

The reports emerged as the couple failed to post any pictures on their fifth wedding anniversary on Friday.

Harry, 38, has a room kept on standby for him at a leading hotel chain in Montecito, close to the couple’s £12million mansion, it has been reported.

He occasionally stays there without wife Meghan, 41, sources say.

Harry is also said to stay at the exclusive San Vicente Bungalows, a private members club in Los Angeles, after going to a gym class called Barry’s Bootcamp nearby.

According to sources, Harry regards it as “an escape place”.

The West Hollywood club has a strict privacy policy, with guests forbidden to take pictures inside the venue and stickers placed over their phone cameras when they arrive.

They are also told not to discuss anything members or their guests witness during their visit.

And they are banned from approaching or interrupting other members inside the clubhouse.

Annual fees are £3,200 and applicants must be vetted by a panel that is rumoured to include actress Julia Roberts.

A spokesperson for Archewell denied the claims.

Andy back in saddle

PRINCE Andrew raises a smile as he rides out with his brother Edward, the Duke of Edinburgh.

The Duke of York, 63, is battling to stay put after the King told him to leave 30-room Royal Lodge in the Windsor grounds.

3 Prince Andrew and Edward went for a horse ride accompanied by grooms in Windsor Credit: Richard Gillard

But Andrew, seemed in good spirits as the brothers rode their horses near the home.
